ToroidZip — Roadmap
===================

## Status: Milestone 2 complete

---

### Milestone 1 — Baseline encoder ✓
- Anchor + ratio computation
- Boundary classification (Identity / Normal / Boundary-Zero / Boundary-Inf)
- Raw float64 ratio stream with periodic re-anchoring (default K=256)
- Lossless round-trip decoder
- Tests passing, benchmarks wired
- CLI scaffold

### Milestone 2 — Entropy coding ✓
- rANS (range Asymmetric Numeral Systems) encoder/decoder
- Three stream versions: v1 (raw), v2 (lossless rANS), v3 (quantized rANS)
- Quantization: N-bit log-space mapping, precision range [1, 30]
- Payload tiers: uint8 / uint16 / uint32 per ratio payload
- DriftCompensate (Mode B): Kahan log-space product accumulator
- `AnalyzeDrift`: per-interval, per-mode error report with recommendation
- `AnalyzePrecision`: auto-select precision bits from data distribution
- `SigFigsToBits` / `BitsToSigFigs`: sig-fig ↔ bit-depth conversion
- CLI expanded: `analyze` subcommand, `--entropy-mode`, `--sig-figs`,
  `--precision`, `--auto`, `--lossy` flags
- Coverage: 87.6%

### Milestone 3 — Benchmarking
Compare against: raw float64, delta encoding, zstd, brotli, fpzip

Target data classes (benchmark dataset suite already implemented in
`codec/bench_test.go`):
1. Sensor stream — slow sinusoidal drift, IoT/logger
2. Financial walk — log-normal RW with 1% regime jumps
3. Scientific multi-scale — values oscillate across 12 decades (1e-6..1e6)
4. Volatile series — 98% stable, 2% ×10/÷10 shock events
5. Near-constant — σ≈0.01%, max-compression noise floor
6. Neural weight proxy — Gaussian mixture at ±0.01 and ±0.1 layer centres

Metrics: compression ratio, encode MB/s, decode MB/s

